Brigham Young University-Idaho 2024-(PROJECTED CLASS OF 2026) BA in Data Science

title: Alex J. Tovar’s Resume
text:
Objective


My name is Alex Tovar, I’m currently challenging myself to pursue a Data Science degree by mastering tools, such as libraries, programming languages, advanced mathematics, and methods to research data-driven knowledge to make decisions. Also, emphasizing in Machine Learning and Applied Mathematics.

title: Alex J. Tovar’s Resume
text:
Experience


Programmed with Java – 2 years Developed skills with programming fundamentals, concepts, algorithms, and tools such as VSCODE.


Tropical Smoothie – 1 year June (2023) – September (2024) MacDonald’s – (½) year Summer (2023) & Summer (2024)


Worked both jobs in the summer handling up to 55-64 hour weeks collaborating, maintaining logistics, solving problems, and working in a fast-paced environment.

title: Alex J. Tovar’s Resume
text:
Attributes


Bilingual (Spanish) Disciplined Self-motivated/Driven Problem Solver Team Collaboration Analytical Skills Adaptable

title: Alex J. Tovar’s Resume
text:
Extracurriculars


Data Science Society Projects Currently Contributing to the “Blood Test” project, to gain experience in a simulated and collaborative environment. Through handling data, data visualization, researching trends, and writing reports


Programmer (Python, R, SQL) Diversifying in practical programming languages to collaborate on more projects in the future. As well as contributing to repositories on GitHub to build and sharpen collaboration and problem-solving skills
